Pop the @sweet potato wedges{450%g} onto a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat evenly.

Roast on the top shelf of your #oven{} until soft and golden, ~{15-17%minutes}. Turn halfway!

Pop the @chicken mini fillets{280%g} into a #bowl{}. Drizzle on a splash of @oil{}, season with @salt{} and sprinkle on the @Mississippi style spice mix{1%pack}.

Mix the spices through the chicken.

Heat a #frying pan{} over medium-high heat (no oil!).

Add the chicken pieces and brown all over, about ~{5%minutes} on each side.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, zest the @lime{1}(zested) and mix it with the @creme fraiche{100%g}.

Mix the @onion marmalade{20%g} with the @fresh chilli jam{1%pack}.

Cut the lime in half.

When the chicken is cooked, remove from the heat and add a squeeze of lime juice and the @baby spinach{125%g} to the pan.

Toss to combine and just soften the spinach.

Pop all of your ingredients in the middle of your table.

Smear your wrap with onion chilli jam and place the @super soft tortillas with whole wheat{4} and the chicken and spinach in the middle.

Drizzle on some limey crème fraiche and roll it up!

Dip your wedges in the left over crème fraiche!